papers.title: Additively manufactured ultra-high vacuum chamber for portable quantum technologies
papers.relevance: UHV chambers are essential for superconducting qubit experiments; this paper demonstrates 3D-printed UHV chambers that can maintain 1e-10 mbar pressures, relevant for portable quantum technologies including potential SC qubit applications

summary: The blog post mentions circuitQED in a section about prompt autocompletion, and discusses an additively manufactured UHV chamber that can maintain ultra-high vacuum conditions. While no direct superconducting qubit papers are cited, the UHV chamber technology is relevant to SC qubit experiments which require ultra-high vacuum environments. The circuitQED mention indicates the author's familiarity with the field.
